SUMMARY
-----------------------------------
CURL          → speaks HTTP/HTTPS properly, best for web APIs
NETCAT        → raw TCP/UDP, no protocol, most flexible
OPENSSL       → like netcat but handles encryption
NMAP          → doesn't connect to talk, just knocks on doors
TELNET        → old curl/netcat, no encryption
------------------
REWORLD USAGE

# Step 1: discover what's running on a server
nmap -sV -p- target.com

# Step 2: check if port 80 is responding
nc -zv target.com 80

# Step 3: grab the webpage
curl -v http://target.com

# Step 4: check SSL certificate
openssl s_client -connect target.com:443






